<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8077] Replication can still cause index corruption.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8077</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Bah. Somehow a critical part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7134&quot; title=&quot;Replication can still cause index corruption.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7134&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7134&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; did not get in with the commit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;       &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (slowFileExists(indexDir, fname)) {
-        LOG.info(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Skipping move file - it already exists:&quot;&lt;/span&gt; + fname);
-        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
+        LOG.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Cannot complete replication attempt because file already exists:&quot;&lt;/span&gt; + fname);
+        
+        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// we fail - we downloaded the files we need, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; we can&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;t move one in, we can&apos;&lt;/span&gt;t
&lt;/span&gt;+        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// count on the correct index
&lt;/span&gt;+        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;;
       }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
